1905858268.text: "The discovery that ACE inhibitors do not block the formation of all Ang II, such as that from Ang I via chymase and other non ACE enzymes, and/or that from angiotensinogen via non renin pathways, and Ang II levels persist during long-term ACE inhibitor therapy, fueled the concept that the combination of ACE inhibition and AT 1 receptor blockade may produce more complete blockade of the deleterious effects of Ang II and produce greater benefits."
